# TravelOps AI Python Client SDK

A python library to interact with the TravelOps AI Autonomous Travel Operations Platform API.

## Installation

You can install the SDK in editable mode during development:

```bash
pip install -e ./travelops-sdk
```

## Quick Start

### 1. Initialize Client & Authenticate
```python
from travelops_sdk import TravelOpsClient

# Initialize client
client = TravelOpsClient(base_url="http://localhost:8000")

# Register a user
client.register(
    email="passenger@travelops.ai",
    password="SecurePassword123",
    name="Jane Passenger",
    role="passenger"
)

# Login to get JWT authorization context
client.login(email="passenger@travelops.ai", password="SecurePassword123")
```

### 2. Operations & Sessions
```python
# Create a new agent operations session
session = client.create_session()
session_id = session["session_id"]
print(f"Session initialized: {session_id}")

# Send user message query to trigger Intent Parsing
response = client.send_message(
    session_id=session_id,
    message="Search for sleeper buses from Hyderabad to Bangalore tomorrow"
)
print("Assistant:", response["response"])

# Run the planned workflow graph asynchronously in the background
client.run_session_workflow(session_id)
```

### 3. Monitoring & Disruption Recovery
```python
# Check real-time workflow state and execution timeline
details = client.get_session_details(session_id)
print(f"Workflow State: {details.workflow_state}")

# Fetch full developer studio timeline details and agent health statuses
studio = client.get_session_studio_details(session_id)
print("Estimated Session Cost (USD):", studio["metrics"]["estimated_cost_usd"])

# Publish disruptions to test autonomous event recovery checks
client.publish_event(
    event_type="BusCancelled",
    payload={
        "session_id": session_id,
        "operator_name": "VRL Travels",
        "route_id": "route_hyd_blr_1",
        "cancelled_at": "2026-06-28T20:00:00Z"
    }
)
```

### 4. Admin and Telemetry
```python
# Retrieve global LLM usage cost and tool registries count
metrics = client.get_observability_metrics()
print(f"Total USD Spent: {metrics.total_cost_usd}")
```
